{
  "texts": [
    "Research indicates that STEM teachers in China, whether as curriculum developers, implementers of novel teaching practices, or facilitators of student-centred STEM learning, face significant pressure and confront difficulties adapting to these reforms (Dong et al. 2020).",
    "Several studies, such as Zhang and Sun (2018) and Dong et al. (2020), have recognized the role of STEM teachers as multifaceted and demanding.",
    "Teachers are motivated to pursue professional development opportunities in STEM education to overcome these challenges (Rehman et al. 2024b; Huang et al. 2022).",
    "These professional development projects are necessary to integrate STEM successfully into the classroom environment (Xie et al. 2021).",
    "Across China, various STEM training initiatives have been launched in numerous cities, ensuring the importance of equipping teachers with the necessary pedagogical skills and knowledge (Lin et al. 2022a)."
  ]
}